snippet.textDisplay: Her hair turned blue bc she used Arctic Fox and Arctic Fox has a really strong amount of blue pigment in it and it overpowers the yellow. I think most of their colors run in the tone of blue though bc even their black isn’t black it’s like a pure blue black. Their blues/ colors that are mixed with blue are really blue and their colors based with red are pink as hell so you have to lift the hair to a yellow level maybe like a 6-7 not a 8-10 level. I’ve used a lot of attic fox and other semi permanent hair colors and it honestly isn’t that great. It has a rep for not turning the color that they say it’s going to.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm a hairstylist and I have had green hair for over 6 months. Her hair turned blue on the ends because most green semi permanents are formulated to go over yellow hair. They're more blue-based so that when they go onto the yellow hair they are true-to-tone and since her ends were lacking that remaining yellow pigment contribution there was nothing to balance out the blue. Hope that helped :) p.s I've been a fan since before hair school you're doing a great job on educating the masses
snippet.textOriginal: I'm a hairstylist and I have had green hair for over 6 months. Her hair turned blue on the ends because most green semi permanents are formulated to go over yellow hair. They're more blue-based so that when they go onto the yellow hair they are true-to-tone and since her ends were lacking that remaining yellow pigment contribution there was nothing to balance out the blue. Hope that helped :) p.s I've been a fan since before hair school you're doing a great job on educating the masses

snippet.textDisplay: arctic fox’s phantom green is primarily blue based. that’s why it can dye or fade blue. i usually combat this by adding one of their lighter pure green dyes or a tiny bit of one of their yellows. hope this helps explain! i’ve had green using this dye multiple times and if done properly (DO A STRAND TEST) it can turn out a beautiful perfect emerald green look. as well, obviously it always helps to have yellower blonde versus pure white blonde. 💚💚💚

snippet.textDisplay: I've been using Manic Panic Enchanted Forest for 5 or so years now. It's the BEST green. Arctic Fox's Phantom Green is meh not that pretty and washes out first wash. Enchanted Forest is ridiculously pigmented so it stains every single thing it touches lol but same goes for the hair, it's not going anywhere once it's on. You don't even have to lighten/destroy your hair too much to get good payoff. I've been mixing it with MP Electric Lizard to get brighter shades of green.
